The '''Azzameen family''' was a family of traders who owned a small shipping business, the [[Twin Suns Transport Services/Legends|Twin Suns Transport Services]].

==History==
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the Azzameen family had a contract with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] to deliver [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]] to one of the Alliance bases serving as a [[Hospital (XQ2 Platform)|hospital]] for Rebels wounded on [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. During one such trip, the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] [[Corrupter (Imperial-class)|''Corrupter'']] arrived and [[Battle of Hospital|attacked]] both the Alliance forces and the family vessels. In the aftermath of that battle the family was then declared traitors to the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] and a warrant for capture was issued against them.

The Azzameens took what they could from their base and escaped before the Imperials arrived and [[Imperialization of Azzameen assets|took control]] of their shipyards and their base. The Azzameens found refuge on-board the [[Mon Calamari Star Cruiser/Legends|Mon Calamari Star Cruiser]] [[Defiance/Legends|''Defiance'']]. While the youngest son, Ace, enlisted with the Rebels as a fighter pilot, the rest of the family concentrated on getting back at the Viraxo and rebuilding the company.

Their first act was to [[Rescue of Antan Azzameen|raid]] the [[Viraxo Industries (platform)|''Viraxo'' station]] where Antan Azzameen was being held. Later Aeron recruited Ace to make a little run to [[Mission to the Saila Na system|pick-up]] a [[Damaged Viper probe droid|damaged]] [[Probe droid/Legends|probe droid]] in the [[Saila Na system/Legends|Saila Na system]] to help keep track of the Viraxo. After an [[Assassination attempt on K'Armyn Viraxo|attempted assassination]] of K'Armyn Viraxo that turned-out to be a trap, they focused more on rebuilding their family business. They attacked at least two Viraxo supply depots in the next couple months for cargo to sell to the Rebels. During the first raid they discovered that the Viraxo were shipping arms for [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]]; this discovery led to a quick strike against an Imperial Communications Station to plant a listening device on a satellite to better monitor the Viraxo-Black Sun alliance.

Ace had to lead one raid to bust Emon out of prison, and he later evaded the guns of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] [[Super Star Destroyer/Legends|Super Star Destroyer]] to rescue Aeron from a base in the [[Vergesso Asteroids/Legends|Vergesso Asteroids]] about to fall to an Imperial [[Battle of the Bajic Shipyards|assault]]. After the Rebellion came under [[Mission to meet Bothan delegation|attack]] from [[Unidentified mercenary (Falcon's Nest mercenaries)|mercenaries]] claiming to be working for the [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustans]], Ace and Aeron were tasked with [[Reconnaissance of mercenary base|finding]] their base, as their freighters would draw less attention than an Alliance ship. They found the base (after a brief visit to an Imperial Test firing facility in the [[Carida system/Legends|Carida system]], courtesy of some altered nav logs) and it turned out to be their old home station. Now that their mission was personal, the Alliance had no trouble recruiting Aeron and Emon to help them reclaim the station and expose the mercenaries. During the [[Battle of Azzameen Station|battle]] Emon spotted his uncle Antan's personal ship fleeing the mercenary base. Ace also recovered the Azzameen Family Crest during this endeavor and put it on display at his quarters as part of his collection.

They didn't have time to investigate their suspicions however; shortly after the battle, Antan informed them that Thomaas and Galin had been captured by the Imperials at the Rebel hospital and sent to a [[Kessel Station|space station]] orbiting [[Kessel/Legends|Kessel]]. Though they attempted to [[Mission to Kessel Station|rescue]] them, they were unsuccessful: an [[Devastator/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] emerged from hyperspace and Antan revealed that he had led his family into a trap as part of a deal with the Empire. He escaped, and so did his niece and nephews with the help of [[Dunari]]. Ace would later go on to fight at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]].

The Azzameen family owned and operated a number of vessels, including two [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighters]]: ''[[Sabra]]'' and ''[[Selu]]'', as well as the [[YT-2000 light freighter/Legends|YT-2000 light freighter]] ''[[Otana/Legends|Otana]]''. The family also owned the [[Firespray-31-class patrol and attack craft/Legends|''Firespray-31''-class patrol and attack craft]] ''[[Andrasta]]'', the [[GR-75 medium transport/Legends|GR-75 medium transport]] ''[[Vasudra]]'', the modified [[Action IV transport]] ''[[Big Score]]'', and several [[Toscan 8-Q starfighter]]s.

